<a href="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/t/keyboard-and-mouse-as-a-controller-again/469218" class="inline-onebox">Keyboard and Mouse as a controller... (again)</a>.   So I looked for Java adaptations with a bit of chatgpt and vscode tutorials on youtube</p>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":14,"updated_at":"2025-06-04T23:27:55.313Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":405,"readers_count":404,"score":91.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":502820,"topic_slug":"keyboard-for-drive","display_username":"Noah","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://www.chiefdelphi.com/t/keyboard-and-mouse-as-a-controller-again/469218","internal":true,"reflection":false,"title":"Keyboard and Mouse as a controller... (again)","clicks":23}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":19235,"username":"Skyehawk","name":"Skye Leake","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/skyehawk/{size}/179363_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":73940,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/keyboard-for-drive/502820/3","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3646105,"name":"Nathan Zhou","username":"NathanZhou","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/nathanzhou/{size}/225374_2.png","created_at":"2025-06-04T23:42:56.282Z","cooked":"<p>More detail here is needed. However one issue I am aware of is pygame window needs to be in focus. That means and has to be on top. This is especially important after you click enable on <span class="abbreviation">DS<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Driver Station"></template></span> as window focus will go to <span class="abbreviation">DS<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Driver Station"></template></span>. You need to click on pygame window to have your input captured. Otherwise nothing will work.</p>
<p>Also on <code>inst.setServer("127.0.0.1")</code> in that python script you need to change that to your roboRIO IP address.</p>
<p>It would also be helpful if you have your java code available.</p>","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"posts_count":14,"updated_at":"2025-06-04T23:43:29.691Z","reply_count":2,"reply_to_post_number":3,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":368,"readers_count":367,"score":98.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":502820,"topic_slug":"keyboard-for-drive","display_username":"Nathan Zhou","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":73940,"username":"Noah01","name":"Noah","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/n/b38774/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":66330,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Fennekinü¶ä is so cute!"},"post_url":"/t/keyboard-for-drive/502820/4","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3646143,"name":"Noah","username":"Noah01","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/n/b38774/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-06-05T00:05:48.060Z","cooked":"<p>In reality I didn‚Äôt understand how to use pygame, the only thing I developed was a class within my code in vscode that sent to the networktable when my key was pressed, I don‚Äôt have the complete code in git but I‚Äôll send at least the part of the class</p>","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"posts_count":14,"updated_at":"2025-06-05T00:05:48.060Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":4,"quote_count":0,"i