import java.awt.event.KeyListener;
import javax.swing.JFrame;

public class KeyboardReader extends JFrame implements KeyListener {
    private boolean spacePressed = false;

    public KeyboardReader() {
        this.setFocusable(true);
        this.setSize(100, 100);
        this.setVisible(true);
        this.addKeyListener(this);
    }

    public boolean isSpacePressed() {
        return spacePressed;
    }

    @Override
    public void keyPressed(KeyEvent e) {
        if (e.getKeyCode() == KeyEvent.VK_SPACE) {
            spacePressed = true;
        }
    }

    @Override
    public void keyReleased(KeyEvent e) {
        if (e.getKeyCode() == KeyEvent.VK_SPACE) {
            spacePressed = false;
        }
    }

    @Override

</code></pre>","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"posts_count":14,"updated_at":"2025-06-05T00:09:48.055Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":4,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":302,"readers_count":301,"score":65.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":502820,"topic_slug":"keyboard-for-drive","display_username":"Noah","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":66330,"username":"NathanZhou","name":"Nathan Zhou","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/nathanzhou/{size}/225374_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":73940,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/keyboard-for-drive/502820/6","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3646245,"name":"Nathan Zhou","username":"NathanZhou","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/nathanzhou/{size}/225374_2.png","created_at":"2025-06-05T01:39:28.603Z","cooked":"<p>What your code is trying to do here is capture local keystroke. Unfortunately, roboRIO don‚Äôt have a keyboard attached so this will not work.</p>
<p>my pygame speaks <a href="https://docs.wpilib.org/en/stable/docs/software/networktables/networktables-intro.html" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">NetworkTables</a>. Keyboard are treated as buttons and mouse movement are treated as analogue input. You need to subscribe to these values and have your actuators react to it.</p>","post_number":7,"post_type":1,"posts_count":14,"updated_at":"2025-06-05T01:39:28.603Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":6,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":241,"readers_count":240,"score":73.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":502820,"topic_slug":"keyboard-for-drive","display_username":"Nathan Zhou","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://docs.wpilib.org/en/stable/docs/software/networktables/networktables-intro.html","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"What is NetworkTables ‚Äî FIRST Robotics Competition documentation","clicks":6}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":73940,"username":"Noah01","name":"Noah","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/n/b38774/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":66330,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Fennekinü¶ä is so cute!"},"post_url":"/t/keyboard-for-drive/502820/7","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3646280,"name":"","username":"LHACK4142","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/lhack4142/{size}/196107_2.png","created_at":"2025-06-05T03:26:30.193Z","cooked":"<p>yup I can concur that this is right.<br>
You can also set up a trigger to bind commands to seeing things in networktables.  our code, which supports keyboard controls, is at <a href="https://github.com/aesatchien/FRC2429_2025" class="inline-onebox">GitHub - aesatchien/FRC2429_2025: Python code for FRC 2429's 2025 robot(s)</a>; it‚Äôs probably less easy to understand than <a class="mention" href="/u/nathanzhou">@NathanZhou</a> 's though.  Note that polling all this stuff takes up some loop time.  It did save us a few times at Tidal when the controller disconnected though.</p>","post_number":8,"post_type":1,"posts_count":14,"updated_at":"2025-06-05T03:26:30.193Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":7,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":3,"reads":211,"readers_count":210,"score":57.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":502820,"topic_slug":"keyboard-for-drive","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://github.com/aesatchien/FRC2429_2025","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"GitHub - aesatchien/FRC2429_2025: Python code for FRC 2429's 2025 robot(s)","clicks":3}],"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":66330,"username":"NathanZhou","name":"Nathan Zhou","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/nathanzhou/{size}/225374_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":58301,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"coder in the corner"},"post_url":"/t/keyboard-for-drive/502820/8","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3646303,"name":"Ezra","username":"Strflightmight","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/strflightmight/{size}/261969_2.png","created_at":"2025-06-05T04:25:51.952Z","cooked":"<p>This is our code for it: <a href="https://github.com/Programming-TRIGON/RobotCode2025/blob/main/src%2Fmain%2Fpython%2Fkeyboard_to_nt.py" class="inline-onebox" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">RobotCode2025/src/main/python/keyboard_to_nt.py at main ¬∑ Programming-TRIGON/RobotCode2025 ¬∑ GitHub</a></p>
<p>This code just runs in the background on the computer and publishes all keys to the nt. We use it with this <a href="https://github.com/Programming-TRIGON/TRIGONLib/blob/main/src%2Fmain%2Fjava%2Forg%2Ftrigon%2Fhardware%2Fmisc%2FKeyboardController.java" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">Keyboard Controller class</a>.</p>","post_number":9,"post_type":1,"posts_count":14,"updated_at":"2025-06-05T04:25:51.952Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":188,"readers_count":187,"score":67.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":502820,"topic_slug":"keyboard-for-drive","display_username":"Ezra","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://github.com/Programming-TRIGON/RobotCode2025/blob/main/src%2Fmain%2Fpython%2Fkeyboard_to_nt.py","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"RobotCode2025/src/main/python/keyboard_to_nt.py at main ¬∑ Programming-TRIGON/RobotCode2025 ¬∑ GitHub","clicks":8},{"url":"https://github.com/Programming-TRIGON/TRIGONLib/blob/main/src%2Fmain%2Fjava%2Forg%2Ftrigon%2Fhardware%2Fmisc%2FKeyboardController.java","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"TRIGONLib/src/main/java/org/trigon/hardware/misc/KeyboardController.java at main ¬∑ Programming-TRIGON/TRIGONLib ¬∑ GitHub","clicks":3}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":2}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":62434,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"5990 | Programmer, Electronics Lead, and Driver"},"post_url":"/t/keyboard-for-drive/502820/9","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":2}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":2,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3646311,"name":"","username":"EmerqldWither","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/emerqldwither/{size}/226176_2.png","created_at":"2025-06-05T04:41:17.537Z","cooked":"<p>Easiest way that we have done it is to use a program called <a href="https://github.com/djlastnight/KeyboardSplitterXbox" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">KeyboardSplitter</a>, and it converts a keyboard into an Xbox controller detected by the <span class="abbreviation">DS<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Driver Station"></template></span>.</p>
<p>In years past, we have used a mechanical numpad as an operator controller by binding the buttons on it to Xbox buttons.</p>","post_number":10,"post_type":1,"posts_count":14,"updated_at":"2025-06-05T04:41:17.537Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":169,"readers_count":168,"score":88.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":502820,"topic_slug":"keyboard-for-drive","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://github.com/djlastnight/KeyboardSplitterXbox","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"GitHub - djlastnight/KeyboardSplitterXbox: Creates up to 4 virtual xbox 360 controllers and feeds them via one or more keyboards.","clicks":7}],"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":53274,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"1672 Programming/Electrical Officer"},"post_url":"/t/keyboard-for-drive/502820/10","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3646313,"name":"","username":"some-guy","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/some-guy/{size}/236378_2.png","created_at":"2025-06-05T04:44:20.509Z","cooked":"<p>Instead of using NetworkTables, we wrote a python script that uses the vjoy library to create a virtual controller, which the robot can then see as raw HID buttons. The window does not need to be focused. This was very robust and performed well at 4 different competitions.</p>
<p>There was also an earlier version of this file that used the vgamepad library to emulate an Xbox 360 controller, but we ran out of buttons.</p>
<p>Latest (vjoy) version:<br>
